Title : Livoberezhnyi Masyv
Text : {{Other uses|Livoberezhna (disambiguation){{!}}Livoberezhna}}
[[File:Вулиця Анатолія Луначарського (Київ) 5.JPG|thumb|300px|Livoberezhna's high-rise residential buildings near the [[Livoberezhna (Kiev Metro)|metro station]].]]

'''Livoberezhnyi Masyv''' ({{lang-uk|Лівобережний масив}}) or commonly known as '''Livoberezhna''' ({{lang-uk|Лівобережна}}) is a residential neighborhood of the [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] capital [[Kiev]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Kyiv, A historical overview|last=Kudrytskyi|first=A. V.|year=1982|publisher=Ukrainian Soviet Encyclopedia|location=[[Kiev|Kyiv]]|isbn=|language=Ukrainian|page=}}</ref> The neighborhood is administratively a part of the [[Dnipro Raion, Kiev|Dnipro Raion]], and is located on the [[Left-bank Ukraine|city's left bank]] (which it is named for).

The neighborhood is surrounded by the [[Dnieper River|Dnipro River]] to its west, [[Darnytsia]] to its north and east, [[Berezniaky]] to its southeast, and [[Rusanivka]] to its south. It was created in the 1960s-1970s on the territory of the [[Mykilska Slobidka]], a former settlement on the outskirts of Kiev.<ref>{{cite web|title=Livoberezhnyi masyv|url=http://wek.kiev.ua/uk/Лівобережний_масив|work=WWW Encyclopedia Kyiv|accessdate=29 April 2014|language=Ukrainian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Historical Reference|url=http://dnipr.kievcity.gov.ua/content/mennyu-1.html|work=Dnipro Raion of Kiev City State Administration|accessdate=30 April 2014|language=Ukrainian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mykilska slobidka |url=http://www.oldkyiv.org.ua/data/slobidka.php?lang=ua |work=Site of the History of Kyiv |accessdate=30 April 2014 |language=Ukrainian |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309004512/http://www.oldkyiv.org.ua/data/slobidka.php?lang=ua |archivedate=9 March 2014 |df= }}</ref>

==Transport==
[[File:Броварський проспект Київ 2009 01.JPG|thumb|300px|View of Livoberehzna from the city's right-bank. The [[Kiev Metro Bridge]] is seen in the center.]]

The Livoberezhnyi neighborhood is serviced by the [[Livoberezhna (Kiev Metro)|Livoberezhna]] station of the [[Kiev Metro]]'s [[Sviatoshynsko-Brovarska Line]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Livoberezhna|url=http://www.metro.kiev.ua/node/159|work=[[Kiev Metro|Kyiv Metropoliten]]|accessdate=29 April 2014|language=Ukrainian}}</ref> where a number of [[Kyivpastrans|city busses]] and [[marshrutka]]s connect. In addition, the [[Kiev Urban Electric Train]] has a [[flag stop]] located in walking distance from the metro station.

==Attractions==
The [[International Exhibition Centre]], Ukraine's largest expo building,<ref>{{cite web|title=History of International Exhibition Centre|url=http://www.iec-expo.com.ua/en/history-of-iec.html|work=International Exhibition Centre|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> is located on the neighborhood's western portion. In addition, the 27-story "Turist" (Tourist) Hotel is located in the neighborhood in direct proximity to the metro station. The [[Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church]]'s main [[Patriarchal Cathedral of the Resurrection of Christ|patriarchal cathedral]] is also located in the neighborhood.

